This paper deals with the complexity of reasoning with a knowledge representation called Generalized First Order Decision Diagrams (GFODD) which is useful in decision theoretic planning in relational domains. This topic falls under the area of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with knowledge representation and reasoning. The paper also involves studying the complexity of computational problems, which is related to the area of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The use of decision diagrams also relates to the area of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also deals with the equivalence problem, which is related to the area of Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper involves studying the polynomial hierarchy, which is related to the area of Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
